<paragraph id="7284567B98792F4CC7872856A6C2E171" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="A3D7A1003616950C2F833535CF9A4B6C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Italy. Liguria.</emphasis>
Sanremo (Imperia), San Romolo (WGS84 43.84670N, 
<geoCoordinate id="D0D4DD3839AF437E9206246F6B52B783" degrees="7.740880" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="7.74088">7.740880E</geoCoordinate>
), pendici del Monte Bignone, margine della strada verso Sanremo, 570 m, 28 May 2021, 
<emphasis id="5E9589E9CF3E1E7A868D79D46841F904" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">M. Ottonello, B. Cera, S. Orsenigo</emphasis>
(PAV).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3707F1E8D2DF9A7B053E00E3B21BE5F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="method">
<paragraph id="96A70E3588AEE18BF32C218F95636048" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4CE390C2F6365B49E7AD286CB5888A47" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 °C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine for 7-8 minutes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1D114832AAFEC8101118FABD1529250" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="observations">
<paragraph id="C77FB934252CBB88A72EFA7F6AB322F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4DB58AC19CB663086EDCE4E90396C5B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="95183AA95B027B2454DFCDF44E6417BD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hieracium tenuiflorum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuiflorum">
<emphasis id="52A53C27908E82857CDA1138C70D924C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hieracium tenuiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a south European perennial species (
<bibRefCitation id="1E598265723755B2A46EB232D126D570" author="Gottschlich, G" editor="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="3, Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1138 - 1195" refId="B18" refString="Gottschlich, G, 2018. Hieracium. In: Pignatti, S, Ed., Flora d'Italia Vol. 3, Edagricole, Bologna: 1138 - 1195" title="Hieracium." volumeTitle="Flora d'Italia Vol." year="2018">Gottschlich 2018</bibRefCitation>
). It was originally described for Monte Bignone, Monte Ceppo, and Monte Arpetta (
<bibRefCitation id="02A9DF4D72DFD12633A3EFE2EEDF470E" author="Bicknell, C" journalOrPublisher="Pietro Gibelli ed, Bordighera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B7" refString="Bicknell, C, 1896. Flora of Bordighera and San Remo. Pietro Gibelli ed, Bordighera" title="Flora of Bordighera and San Remo." year="1896">Bicknell 1896</bibRefCitation>
), in the Ligurian Alps. In Italy, this species is widespread throughout the Alps and pre-Alps, but it occurs also in the northern and central Apennines south up to Abruzzo (
<bibRefCitation id="ADBBA4745C82A8F91B59824174F0F877" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" author="Bartolucci, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="179 - 303" refId="B5" refString="Bartolucci, F, Peruzzi, L, Galasso, G, Albano, A, Alessandrini, A, Ardenghi, NMG, Astuti, G, Bacchetta, G, Ballelli, S, Banfi, E, Barberis, G, Bernardo, L, Bouvet, D, Bovio, M, Cecchi, L, Di Pietro, R, Domina, G, Fascetti, S, Fenu, G, Festi, F, Foggi, B, Gallo, L, Gottschlich, G, Gubellini, L, Iamonico, D, Iberite, M, Jimenez-Mejias, P, Lattanzi, E, Marchetti, D, Martinetto, E, Masin, RR, Medagli, P, Passalacqua, NG, Peccenini, S, Pennesi, R, Pierini, B, Poldini, L, Prosser, F, Raimondo, FM, Roma-Marzio, F, Rosati, L, Santangelo, A, Scoppola, A, Scortegagna, S, Selvaggi, A, Selvi, F, Soldano, A, Stinca, A, Wagensommer, RP, Wilhalm, T, Conti, F, 2018. An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy. Plant Biosystems 152 (2): 179 - 303, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" title="An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" volume="152" year="2018">Bartolucci et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A32AF4E96B548EBBBDA9D2E70FB4E359" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The chromosome number 2 
<emphasis id="CE78F0393CC80E732A23FB993ADCF5C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 3 
<emphasis id="062001F37D21EEFE9784B29CC445B923" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x</emphasis>
= 27, reported here for the first time, is consistent with observations made in other taxa belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="8F1AC29E5CD787C345B98F0C821133DA" genus="H." lsidName="H. subsp. sect." pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="section" section="Hieracium" species="tenuiflorum" subSpecies="sect.">H. sect. Hieracium</taxonomicName>
, such as those of the 
<taxonomicName id="37B9C4495EDB5740A829EDFB71873E78" genus="H." lsidName="H. murorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="murorum">
<emphasis id="F8E9770A1C8C2A4ABA1F1B69CE88D3E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">H. murorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
aggregate in Italy (
<bibRefCitation id="8373AEA826D11A78B31B8C164DB40D05" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00087114.1996.10797373" author="Selvi, F" journalOrPublisher="Caryologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="287 - 299" refId="B27" refString="Selvi, F, Fiorini, G, 1996. Karyology of Hieracium L. subg. Hieracium (Asteraceae) from Mount Amiata (Central Italy). Caryologia 49: 287 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00087114.1996.10797373" title="Karyology of Hieracium L. subg. Hieracium (Asteraceae) from Mount Amiata (Central Italy)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00087114.1996.10797373" volume="49" year="1996">Selvi and Fiorini 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="46616CD28C9605C6C095A1F78F66F03E" author="Geraci, A" editor="Kamari, G" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="314 - 319" refId="B17" refString="Geraci, A, Di Gristina, E, Schicchi, R, 2007. Reports (1640-1644). In: Kamari, G, Blanche, C, Garbari, F, Eds., Mediterranean chromosome number reports 17. Flora Mediterranea 17: 314 - 319" title="Reports (1640 - 1644)." volume="17" volumeTitle="Mediterranean chromosome number reports 17." year="2007">Geraci et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="80112D939AE5D2B06CB49A22C4B28C32" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" author="Chrtek Jr, J" journalOrPublisher="Annals of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="161 - 178" refId="B10" refString="Chrtek Jr, J, Zahradnicek, J, Krak, K, Fehrer, J, 2009. Genome size in Hieracium subgenus Hieracium (Asteraceae) is strongly correlated with major phylogenetic groups. Annals of Botany 104: 161 - 178, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" title="Genome size in Hieracium subgenus Hieracium (Asteraceae) is strongly correlated with major phylogenetic groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/aob/mcp107" volume="104" year="2009">Chrtek et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
